file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        hashes: {type: string}
        permalink: {type: string}
        references: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        emails: {type: string}
        hashes: {type: string}
        permalink: {type: string}
        references: {type: string}
        resolutions: {type: string}
        subdomains: {type: string}
        votes: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        domains: {type: string}
        permalink: {type: string}
        references: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        domains: {type: string}
        ips: {type: string}
        md5: {type: string}
        permalink: {type: string}
        references: {type: string}
        scans: {type: string}
        sha1: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        hashes: {type: string}
        permalink: {type: string}
        references: {type: string}
        resolutions_domain_list: {type: string}
        resolutions_last_resolved_list: {type: string}
        votes: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of AlienVault ThreatCrowd
  title: AlienVault ThreatCrowd
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Gets threat hashes for a term known to antivirus programs
      parameters:
      - description: The term you send to the antivirus
        example: plugx
        in: query
        name: Antivirus
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ThreatCrowd AntiVirus Report
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Gets threat hashes for a domain
      parameters:
      - description: The domain of a website to check
        example: google.com
        in: query
        name: Domain
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ThreatCrowd Domain Report
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Gets threat hashes for an email address
      parameters:
      - description: The value you send to the antivirus report
        example: william19770319@yahoo.com
        in: query
        name: Email
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ThreatCrowd Email Report
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Gets threat hashes for a file hash
      parameters:
      - description: The file hash to check
        example: 000269bab6833d37ca78b7445c9a3373
        in: query
        name: File Hash
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ThreatCrowd File Hash Report
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Gets threat hashes for an IP Address
      parameters:
      - description: The IP in to check out on ThreatCrowd
        example: 127.0.0.1
        in: query
        name: IP Address
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: ThreatCrowd IP Report
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
